cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM

The paper proposes a method for automatic cell counting in microscopic images using a fully convolutional neural network (FCNN) and density regression. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of auxiliary FCNNs for additional supervision and the concatenating framework for multi-scale feature integration suggest a focus on deep learning techniques, which also aligns with the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of immunofluorescent images for experimentation suggests a focus on medical imaging, which aligns with the information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
